Version: 0.1.6
Date: 2026-04-12

Changes:
- Bash tool robustness improvements:
  strips accidental leading shell prompt markers (`>` / `>>`) from
  generated commands and enables `pipefail`, so pipeline failures are
  reported as errors instead of false `exit: 0` success.
- Repeated tool-error self-correction in loop runtime:
  when the same tool call arguments fail repeatedly, Merlion injects
  a correction hint to stop retry loops and re-anchor path discovery
  from the workspace root.
- `.merlion` path guidance hardening:
  repeated-failure correction now explicitly requires project-local
  `${cwd}/.merlion` paths only, and forbids `~/.merlion` and
  `.merlion/<project>/...` path constructions.
- Auth failure remediation UX:
  provider auth/key failures now return actionable guidance including
  `merlion config`, config file location, and supported API key env vars.
- Interactive recovery for invalid/expired key:
  when auth failure occurs, CLI now asks whether to reopen setup wizard;
  in REPL it resumes after reconfiguration, and in one-shot mode it
  retries the user request once after successful reconfiguration.

